question: The "Timor Gap" is located between which two regions?
option4: Timor Island and Democratic Republic of Congo
explanation: Timor Gap is an area of Timor Sea between Australia and Timor Island. Timor Island is divided between independent East Timor and West Timor province of Indonesia. The Timor Gap is part of the Australia-East Timor border, Australia-Indonesia border and East Timor-Indonesia border.
